data.description: Welcome to this charming and spacious home nestled in the heart of Glenshire. This lovely residence offers a generous 3,728 square feet of space, situated on a sizable lot with a wide and mostly level driveway. Light and bright, it has 4 bedrooms, laundry room, flex room and 3 full bathrooms, all designed for comfortable, modern living.  Step inside and you'll be greeted by an inviting interior that seamlessly blends functionality and style. Soaring ceilings, an abundance of natural light and a new wood burning stove create a warm and comfortable space to relax. The open floor plan gives a sense of spaciousness, making it perfect for both living the good life and entertaining.   A well-appointed kitchen features a bay window, modern appliances, ample counter space and storage, making it a central hub for culinary enthusiasts. The center island has a gas 4-burner stove and bar seating for 5, making it easy to prepare meals while conversing with others. The kitchen has access to the side deck through French doors adjacent to the dining area. The side deck leads to a huge front deck for basking in the morning sun, a perfect way to start the day.   The master suite is on the main upstairs level, down the hall from the living/kitchen/dining room and is a true retreat, offering privacy and relaxation with an ensuite bathroom and 3 closets. There are 2 additional good-sized bedrooms and a full bathroom down the hall.  Downstairs offers an office or 4th bedroom along with a flex room with a gas fireplace and access to the covered patio and the large backyard. There is also a laundry room that has a Murphy bed for overflow guests, an expansive folding table, sink and plenty of cabinets for storage. In this space is also a full bathroom and access to the attached 2 car garage with bonus, a “wet room” or workshop! Outside, the property boasts a generous fenced in backyard with grass and mature trees, ideal for outdoor activities, gardening, or simply enjoying the natural beauty of Glenshire. The surrounding area is known for its stunning natural landscapes, providing a tranquil and picturesque backdrop for your new home. A “game shed” is tucked away next to the covered back patio. This fun little shed has an electric mini split, lighting, TV and a futon for year-round use!   On the side yard is a huge tool shed for lawn mowers, shovels, etc. as well as covered storage under the side deck for wood storage or toys, plus access to the driveway from one of the 4 gates. The front yard has lovely mature trees that flower in spring and change color in fall plus a small grass lawn with sprinklers.   This property offers both a peaceful escape and convenient access to the amenities and attractions of the town. Whether you're a nature lover, outdoor enthusiast, or someone seeking a comfortable and spacious home, 11194 Huntsman Leap is a fantastic choice.
